WEBVTT

00:02.419 --> 00:05.798
ABRAHAM: For centuries,
mankind has been the dominant species.

00:06.256 --> 00:11.137
We've domesticated animals,
locked them up, killed them for sport.

00:11.303 --> 00:14.898
But a series of recent events seem
to suggest all across the globe,

00:15.891 --> 00:18.440
animals have decided, "No more."

00:18.602 --> 00:20.229
And so we were hired,

00:20.395 --> 00:22.489
a team of people from
different backgrounds,

00:22.648 --> 00:24.150
with different specialties:

00:24.316 --> 00:26.444
an expert in animal behavior,

00:26.610 --> 00:29.659
a journalist, safari guide,

00:29.821 --> 00:34.247
foreign intelligence agent
and a veterinary pathologist.

00:34.409 --> 00:37.037
Our task: to Hnd out what is
happening with the animals,

00:37.955 --> 00:41.926
why it's happening,
and how to stop it.

00:43.126 --> 00:44.628
NARRATOR: Previously on Zoo:

00:47.714 --> 00:51.264
I think these lions are communicating
with each other, long distance.

00:52.636 --> 00:56.812
Are you willing to join me
and do something about it?

00:56.974 --> 00:58.021
The global pandemic

00:58.183 --> 01:00.936
your father believed was about to
emerge, it has arrived.

01:01.103 --> 01:02.696
You work for Reiden Global.

01:02.854 --> 01:06.358
I know the FBI just issued
a warrant for your arrest.

01:06.525 --> 01:08.744
Give me the Mother Cell,
and I'll see what I can do

01:08.902 --> 01:10.119
about helping you out.

01:10.279 --> 01:11.496
The answer's no.

01:11.947 --> 01:14.075
MITCH: I believe that if we
introduce the Mother Cell

01:14.241 --> 01:19.247
into the DNA of a mutated animal,
we could possibly synthesize a cure.

01:19.413 --> 01:21.666
But we need an animal
who has mutated

01:21.832 --> 01:24.301
and has not been exposed
to the Mother Cell.

01:24.459 --> 01:25.585
Specifically, leopards.

01:25.752 --> 01:28.596
There are some areas in Africa
where there's no Reiden activity.

01:28.755 --> 01:31.508
- Zambia, Africa.
- There is a way to get back to Africa.

01:31.675 --> 01:34.144
Oh, no, you're thinking about
Ray, aren't you?

01:34.303 --> 01:36.977
- Who's Ray?
- Raymond Joseph Endicott.

01:37.139 --> 01:38.561
