- Yeah, let's just not think about that.

28:14.735 --> 28:16.954
These tracks are fresh.

28:18.071 --> 28:19.914
They're leading
away from the den.

28:20.073 --> 28:23.168
Well, if they've gone out for a hunt,
they won't be back till nightfall.

28:24.870 --> 28:26.713
We can watch from the
car until they return.

28:26.872 --> 28:29.421
Or we can wait right here.

28:29.583 --> 28:32.632
All right? If the first one comes
back alone, we'll surprise it.

28:35.881 --> 28:37.633
What?

28:38.133 --> 28:39.555
Ray didn't have to die.

28:39.718 --> 28:40.935
What's that supposed to mean?

28:41.845 --> 28:43.097
Ray didn't have to die.

28:43.931 --> 28:47.105
We should have had a better plan.
No, we should have had any plan at all.

28:47.267 --> 28:49.440
You think I've been reckless?
You've already said that.

28:49.603 --> 28:52.732
- No one's coming up with any ideas.
- That's because you didn't let them.

28:52.898 --> 28:55.026
- Man, that's.
- I don't want any more excuses.

28:55.192 --> 28:56.660
And I'm not questioning
your motives,

28:56.818 --> 28:59.662
but if there's no one
left alive to help you...

28:59.863 --> 29:00.910
[LEOPARD GROWLING]

29:04.743 --> 29:05.790
That's a female.

29:08.205 --> 29:09.405
They must have left her alone.

29:09.539 --> 29:12.918
If that's the case,
then maybe she has a cub inside the den.

29:13.085 --> 29:15.554
A cub would be a lot easier
to deal with than an adult.

29:15.712 --> 29:19.933
But if she does have a cub,
she'll only be gone for a moment.

29:51.081 --> 29:52.128
[UNDERBRUSH RUSTLING]

30:31.913 --> 30:33.165
The cub.

30:33.749 --> 30:35.126
Let's go make the cure.

31:06.448 --> 31:07.574
What happened to the bridge?

31:08.533 --> 31:09.785
The rope's been chewed.

31:09.951 --> 31:12.955
We're going to have to drive
the long way around the river.

31:13.538 --> 31:16.417
If we drive the long
way around the river,

31:16.708 --> 31:18.748
we have to drive through
the Ndube Army's territory.

31:19.461 --> 31:20.963
JAMIE: The Ndube Army?

31:21.129 --> 31:22.809
I'm guessing that's not a real
army, right?

31:22.964 --> 31:24.637
Far from it.

31:24.800 --> 31:27.098
Think of a African Hells Angels.

31:27.260 --> 31:29.308
Except instead of motorcycles
and leather jackets,

31:29.471 --> 31:31.815
they have rifles and machetes.

31:33.183 --> 31:34.856
There's no other way.

31:35.018 --> 31:36.816
Course there isn't.

31:39.856 --> 31:41.529
MITCH: Hey,
we sure this is the best plan?

31:42.901 --> 31:45.154
We should just drive fast,
get the hell through here,

31:45.320 --> 31:46.663
not worry about
the engine noise.

31:46.822 --> 31:49.621
No. We should stay quiet.

31:49.908 --> 31:50.955
[PHONE RINGING]

31:51.410 --> 31:53.003
What is that?

31:54.955 --> 31:56.127
MITCH: It's Chloe's phone.

31:56.289 --> 31:58.508
Must've left it in my pack.

32:00.502 --> 32:02.049
Hello?

32:02.212 --> 32:03.805
MAN [OVER PHONE]: Who is this?

32:04.464 --> 32:07.138
This is Jackson Oz.
I'm a friend of Chloe's. Who is this?

32:07.300 --> 32:08.517
My name is Pascal Cransac.

32:08.677 --> 32:10.554
I work with Chloe at the DGSE.

32:10.720 --> 32:13.064
If you know where she is,
you need to tell me right away.

32:13.223 --> 32:14.850
She's been arrested.

32:15.016 --> 32:17.110
She's fine though.
She's safe. She's...

32:17.269 --> 32:18.486
She's in FBI custody.

32:18.645 --> 32:20.363
- No, she's not.
JACKSON: What do you mean?

32:20.522 --> 32:22.195
- How do you know that?
- It's my job.

32:22.357 --> 32:24.780
The FBI agent who was escorting
her back to New York City

32:24.943 --> 32:27.162
was found dead on the side of the
road, murdered.

32:27.320 --> 32:28.492
Now Chloe's missing.

32:29.406 --> 32:30.999
What's going on?

32:31.158 --> 32:33.001
She's wanted for the
murder of a second agent.

32:33.160 --> 32:34.457
She didn't kill that agent.

32:34.619 --> 32:37.247
I know that and you know that,
but whoever did do the killing...

32:37.414 --> 32:38.461
Has Chloe.

32:38.623 --> 32:41.752
PASCAL: If you hear anything from
her, please call me on this number.

32:41.918 --> 32:44.467
Yes, I will. Of course.

32:44.629 --> 32:46.631
You do the same.

32:49.176 --> 32:52.897
- What is it?
- That fed, Brannigan, he was killed.

32:53.847 --> 32:55.394
Reiden.

32:55.557 --> 32:56.604
It had to be Reiden.

32:58.310 --> 33:02.360
If that is the case,
then what have they done with Chloe?

33:05.984 --> 33:07.064
[NATHALIE SOBBING ON VIDEO]

33:07.194 --> 33:08.696
NATHALIE [ON VIDEO]: No!

33:15.827 --> 33:17.670
Oh, this is good.

33:17.829 --> 33:19.923
You're going to enjoy this.

33:20.665 --> 33:22.905
[ELECTRICITY CRACKLING,
THEN NATHALIE SCREAMING ON VIDEO]

33:30.926 --> 33:31.973
Okay. Stop.

33:33.470 --> 33:36.098
- I'll tell you, but just make him stop.
- You first.

33:40.352 --> 33:41.524
They're in India.

33:41.686 --> 33:43.313
A small town in Rajasthan.

33:43.480 --> 33:45.778
- Why India?
NATHALIE [ON VIDEO]: No, no.

33:45.941 --> 33:49.161
They're looking for a
specific group of leopards,

33:49.319 --> 33:51.617
unaffected by Reiden chemicals.

33:51.780 --> 33:53.953
You've poisoned the animals
everywhere, but not there.

33:54.908 --> 33:56.501
Thank you.

33:57.369 --> 33:59.497
Now, tell him to get the
hell away from my sister.

33:59.663 --> 34:01.791
If you're lying to
me, your sister dies.

34:02.666 --> 34:04.134
They're in India.

34:31.570 --> 34:33.413
