Hold on.

39:00.421 --> 39:02.344
Oh, no, no, no.

39:04.592 --> 39:05.639
[GUNSHOT]

39:13.726 --> 39:16.024
Listen to me carefully.
We don't have much time.

39:16.187 --> 39:17.689
I'm on your side.

39:17.856 --> 39:19.904
Things were never supposed
to happen like this.

39:20.066 --> 39:21.409
It got out of control.

39:21.568 --> 39:23.821
I want...
I need to help fix this.

39:23.987 --> 39:25.034
Let me help you.

39:25.196 --> 39:27.449
Tell me where Jackson
and the others are.

39:27.615 --> 39:29.333
Tell me, so we can help them.

39:30.493 --> 39:32.916
This is another trick
to get me to talk.

39:34.038 --> 39:35.335
No, it's not.

39:35.498 --> 39:38.047
But I'm risking
everything to be here.

39:38.209 --> 39:40.086
I need to know you'll trust me.

39:40.295 --> 39:41.342
[BANOINO ON DOOR]

39:42.338 --> 39:43.858
GASPARD: Open up!
DELAVANE: Look at me.

39:44.048 --> 39:46.517
Look in my eyes.
You're good at this.

39:46.676 --> 39:50.271
Look at me and decide if
I'm telling you the truth.

39:50.430 --> 39:53.183
GASPARD: Unlock this door now!
DELAVANE: What's it gonna be?

39:53.349 --> 39:55.522
Shoot that bastard dead,
then maybe we'll talk.

39:59.939 --> 40:01.657
DELAVANE: We need to go.

40:04.903 --> 40:07.076
My sister, you have to help her.

40:07.238 --> 40:08.740
You have...

40:09.699 --> 40:11.201
I already have.

40:16.247 --> 40:18.295
[MAN SPEAKING IN
FRENCH ON VIDEO]

40:18.625 --> 40:20.144
DELAVANE: They'll take
her to the hospital.

40:20.168 --> 40:21.841
We can call from the road.

40:23.129 --> 40:25.928
If you're lying to
me, I will kill you.

40:29.302 --> 40:33.102
- They're in Zambia.
- Let's go finish what we began.

40:43.942 --> 40:46.115
Looks like we're 10
miles from the hospital.

40:46.277 --> 40:47.824
How's he doing?

40:49.447 --> 40:50.699
ABRAHAM: Not so good.

40:55.453 --> 40:57.205
That's the third one in an hour.

40:57.372 --> 41:01.718
MITCH: Yeah, that's the same pattern
we saw when we were in Boston.

41:02.085 --> 41:03.132
[couc-HING]

41:04.128 --> 41:05.596
We're close, my friend.

41:08.633 --> 41:11.637
The blood, the blood is
coming through the shirt.

41:11.803 --> 41:13.271
Keep pressure on
it, nice and even.

41:14.097 --> 41:15.770
Don't let him pass out.

41:17.058 --> 41:18.150
Maybe we should pull over.

41:18.810 --> 41:20.983
Lot of things I can
handle in a pinch.

41:21.145 --> 41:23.694
Kind of surgery he
needs, not one of them.

41:24.232 --> 41:25.279
[LEOPARD GROWLING]

41:26.943 --> 41:29.196
The cub is impatient, raHki.

41:29.362 --> 41:31.114
You need to give him a name.

41:31.531 --> 41:35.126
Maybe a musical name,
considering how much noise he makes.

41:35.284 --> 41:38.288
Perhaps Bono or Bowie?

41:54.721 --> 41:55.768
JAMIE: What's going on?

41:57.306 --> 41:58.649
Where are they going?

42:00.268 --> 42:02.396
Everybody's leaving town.

42:02.562 --> 42:04.530
Could be a million reasons.

42:05.398 --> 42:06.445
[JACKSON COUGHS]

42:20.621 --> 42:22.840
You're worried about your team.

42:23.791 --> 42:25.134
I need to talk to them.

42:25.293 --> 42:27.170
Reiden will be looking for us.

42:27.336 --> 42:29.054
They'll be monitoring
cell conversations.

42:29.213 --> 42:30.260
If they find you,

42:30.423 --> 42:33.017
they can have an interception
team wheels up in minutes.

42:33.176 --> 42:36.851
Look, I don't even know if
Jackson found the leopard,

42:37.013 --> 42:39.266
or if they made the cure.

42:42.518 --> 42:44.065
Or if they're even alive.

42:44.228 --> 42:45.605
I understand.

42:45.772 --> 42:47.115
But if this goes well,

42:47.273 --> 42:48.445
we'll have the entire weight

42:48.608 --> 42:50.281
of the United States
government behind us.

42:50.443 --> 42:53.743
- Maybe you should do it yourself.
- No.

42:54.072 --> 42:57.326
- You have one thing that I do not.
- What's that?

42:57.867 --> 42:59.619
You've looked it in the eye.

42:59.786 --> 43:01.663
This animal pandemic.

43:01.829 --> 43:04.673
You've even managed to get the
better of it once or twice.

43:05.541 --> 43:10.843
There's one person here
who can make them believe.

43:11.756 --> 43:13.258
And that's you, Chloe.

43:23.017 --> 43:24.064
[PEOPLE SCREAMING]

43:30.316 --> 43:32.193
- Grab the electroporator.
- Oh, my God.

43:32.360 --> 43:34.362
That's why they're all leaving.

43:39.534 --> 43:40.911
We need to get inside now.

43:44.872 --> 43:46.089
Here.

43:47.333 --> 43:49.051
- Hey!
- Open the door! It's an emergency!

43:49.877 --> 43:51.003
My friend needs a doctor!

43:54.882 --> 43:57.010
MAN: The hospital is closed.

44:00.263 --> 44:02.106
Did you hear what I said?

44:02.265 --> 44:03.505
We are abandoning the hospital.

44:03.641 --> 44:05.564
- You have to go elsewhere.
- We don't have time.

44:05.726 --> 44:07.246
- This man's been shot.
- I can't help.

44:07.395 --> 44:10.444
- I suggest you drive him to Nyanga.
- That's four hours at least.

44:10.606 --> 44:13.206
I have lost a dozen colleagues and
more patients than I can count.

44:13.359 --> 44:14.861
I am sorry,
but I cannot help you.

44:15.027 --> 44:18.031
You will help him! You understand me?
You will help...

44:27.331 --> 44:30.005
The last ambulance
leaves in an hour.

44:30.960 --> 44:33.463
I will do the surgery, but beyond
that, you are on your own.

44:34.463 --> 44:36.090
Thank you.

44:36.257 --> 44:38.555
Three units of O-negative
and find some morphine.

44:38.718 --> 44:40.436
It started at the edge of town.

44:40.970 --> 44:43.348
The lions came first,
then the leopards.

44:43.764 --> 44:44.844
When did the attacks begin?

44:44.974 --> 44:47.352
Two days ago. They attacked the
young and the elderly first,

44:47.518 --> 44:49.520
then hospitals where they
were taken for treatment.

44:49.687 --> 44:51.985
